regarding your earlier question for ideas
I feel this is not very tangible (what is the ultimate goal?)
I can dump my expectation for what we will need to do for Termination
so I think first and foremost, we will probably need to wait until the Try trait v2 rfc is further along, because I think it may impact any of our designs or impls
then, I feel that generic member access if without a doubt the way to go with the Result:Err impl of Termination
need to catch up on that
where once we've added generic member access we will have the termination impl always check the &dyn Error type for a StatusCode
or w/e the type is
and if it has one it will use that for the exit code when terminating
I'm not as sure what we should do about StatusCode itself
so I think we should ideally see if we can minimize the dependency between the two features
and make it so Termination "just works" regardless of what extra functionality gets added to StatusCode down the line
because I don't think termination needs to concern itself with doing anything other than passing along a number
you mean ExitCode?
yes
didn't look up the actual type name before talking
